RABIES, FOX, HUMAN EXPOSURE - USA (MASSACHUSETTS)
*************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
Date: Thu, 27 Apr 2000 19:25:49 -0400
From: Donald L. Mahler <donmahler@rcn.com>
Source: Newton Tab and Boston Globe 27 Apr 2000 [edited]

Eight people, including a 3-year old were attacked by a rabid fox in Newton
Center Tuesday. Most of the victims of the attacks reportedly suffered
minor injuries. Police shot fox, and state lab confirmed rabies. Six of the
victims were being treated and the other two were not bitten.
--
Donald L. Mahler MD
